snippet.textDisplay: I couldn't watch all of this because of the horrific picture and finally stopped at the picture of dozens of bears in individual cages barely larger than themselves.  I prioritize human life over animal life, and killing for food is an intrinsic part of the natural order, but I don't prioritize animal welfare over human whims and desires.  I understand opening up available food sources when hundreds of thousands are starving to death, but once that calculus has changed, it's just greed that keeps those policies in place.  I hope COVID-19 causes international pressure that persuades China to change these policies that are not just putting its own people at risk, but people around the world.

I prioritize human life over animal life, and killing for food is an intrinsic part of the natural order, but I don't prioritize animal welfare over human whims and desires.  I understand opening up available food sources when hundreds of thousands are starving to death, but once that calculus has changed, it's just greed that keeps those policies in place.  I hope COVID-19 causes international pressure that persuades China to change these policies that are not just putting its own people at risk, but people around the world.
